    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-11-18T14:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-11-18T14:00:00-05:00" n="285"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d285">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.0146/742a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Second Secretary of Embassy in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Smyth</hi>
                    </persName>), <hi rend="italic">at Peiping</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-11-18T14:00:00-05:00"
                            >November 18, 1939—2 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>259. In connection with the recent announcements of the British and French
                    Governments that they intend to reduce their military forces stationed in north
                    China, the Department requests that Peiping, Shanghai and Tientsin keep it
                    currently informed of pertinent developments in this connection, especially in
                    regard to numerical or other important changes affecting British and French
                    forces in north China and at Shanghai.<note n="13" xml:id="d285fn13">Such
                        information was promptly reported by telegram.</note>
                </p>
                <p>Sent to Peiping. Repeated to Chungking, Shanghai and Tientsin.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Welles</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
